---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="PDLC Redesign · Mollie Cox"
  description="Architecting a four-phase product development lifecycle adopted org-wide across product, design, engineering, and PMM."
>
  <!-- ============================== -->
  <!-- HERO -->
  <!-- ============================== -->
  <section class="case-hero-dark">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 md:px-10 py-20 md:py-28 relative z-10">
      <a
        href="/#work"
        class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.15em] text-cream/60 hover:text-orange transition-colors mb-16"
      >
        ← All work
      </a>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-12 gap-8 md:gap-12 items-start">

        <!-- Text column -->
        <div class="md:col-span-7">
          <p class="eyebrow-light mb-6">Branch · 2025 to 2026</p>

          <h1 class="font-display text-display-lg text-cream leading-[0.95] tracking-tight">
            Redesigning a product development lifecycle<span class="brand-period">.</span>
          </h1>

          <p class="mt-10 text-xl text-cream/80 leading-relaxed max-w-[48ch]">
            A four-phase operating model with named DACI ownership, paired briefs,
            mandatory success metrics before Build, and post-launch decision loops.
            Adopted across product, design, engineering, and PMM.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Artifact column: four phases with two standing threads -->
        <div class="md:col-span-5 flex justify-center md:justify-end items-start mt-8 md:mt-0">
          <div class="case-hero-artifact w-full max-w-sm md:max-w-none">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 480 440" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" role="img" aria-label="Four product development phases with two standing threads, design at the top, customer proximity at the bottom, running across all phases">

              <!-- Subtle grid backdrop -->
              <g opacity="0.06">
                <line stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="0.5" x1="80" y1="6" x2="80" y2="420"/>
                <line stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="0.5" x1="160" y1="6" x2="160" y2="420"/>
                <line stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="0.5" x1="240" y1="6" x2="240" y2="420"/>
                <line stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="0.5" x1="320" y1="6" x2="320" y2="420"/>
                <line stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="0.5" x1="400" y1="6" x2="400" y2="420"/>
              </g>

              <!-- TOP THREAD: Design (orange, dashed, runs across all phases) -->
              <text x="240" y="10" text-anchor="middle" fill="#E13D0F" font-family="'JetBrains Mono', ui-monospace, monospace" font-size="9" letter-spacing="2">DESIGN · STANDING THREAD</text>
              <line x1="60" y1="22" x2="420" y2="22" stroke="#E13D0F" stroke-width="2" stroke-dasharray="4 4" stroke-linecap="round"/>
              <circle cx="240" cy="22" r="4" fill="#E13D0F"/>

              <!-- Phase 01: Discover -->
              <g transform="translate(0, 42)">
                <rect x="60" y="0" width="360" height="68" rx="4" fill="none" stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
                <rect x="62" y="2" width="4" height="64" fill="#E13D0F"/>
                <g transform="translate(100, 34)">
                  <circle cx="0" cy="0" r="14" fill="none" stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="2"/>
                  <circle cx="0" cy="0" r="9" fill="none" stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="1.5"/>
                  <circle cx="0" cy="0" r="4" fill="#E13D0F"/>
                </g>
                <text x="140" y="28" fill="#E13D0F" font-family="'JetBrains Mono', ui-monospace, monospace" font-size="11" font-weight="500" letter-spacing="2">01</text>
                <text x="140" y="46" fill="#F4EFE5" font-family="'JetBrains Mono', ui-monospace, monospace" font-size="12" letter-spacing="2" opacity="0.95">DISCOVER</text>
                <text x="140" y="60" fill="#F4EFE5" font-family="'JetBrains Mono', ui-monospace, monospace" font-size="9" letter-spacing="1" opacity="0.55">Signed problem brief</text>
              </g>

              <!-- Connector arrow Discover -> Plan -->
              <g transform="translate(240, 120)">
                <line x1="0" y1="0" x2="0" y2="12" stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" opacity="0.5"/>
                <polyline points="-4,8 0,12 4,8" fill="none" stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" opacity="0.5"/>
              </g>

              <!-- Phase 02: Plan -->
              <g transform="translate(0, 140)">
                <rect x="60" y="0" width="360" height="68" rx="4" fill="none" stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
                <rect x="62" y="2" width="4" height="64" fill="#9B40C4"/>
                <g transform="translate(100, 34)">
                  <rect x="-12" y="-10" width="10" height="14" fill="none" stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
                  <rect x="2" y="-10" width="10" height="14" fill="none" stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
                  <line x1="-9" y1="-5" x2="-5" y2="-5" stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="1"/>
                  <line x1="-9" y1="-1" x2="-5" y2="-1" stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="1"/>
                  <line x1="5" y1="-5" x2="9" y2="-5" stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="1"/>
                  <line x1="5" y1="-1" x2="9" y2="-1" stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="1"/>
                </g>
                <text x="140" y="28" fill="#9B40C4" font-family="'JetBrains Mono', ui-monospace, monospace" font-size="11" font-weight="500" letter-spacing="2">02</text>
                <text x="140" y="46" fill="#F4EFE5" font-family="'JetBrains Mono', ui-monospace, monospace" font-size="12" letter-spacing="2" opacity="0.95">PLAN</text>
                <text x="140" y="60" fill="#F4EFE5" font-family="'JetBrains Mono', ui-monospace, monospace" font-size="9" letter-spacing="1" opacity="0.55">Paired briefs + metrics</text>
              </g>

              <!-- Connector arrow Plan -> Build -->
              <g transform="translate(240, 218)">
                <line x1="0" y1="0" x2="0" y2="12" stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" opacity="0.5"/>
                <polyline points="-4,8 0,12 4,8" fill="none" stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" opacity="0.5"/>
              </g>

              <!-- Phase 03: Build -->
              <g transform="translate(0, 238)">
                <rect x="60" y="0" width="360" height="68" rx="4" fill="none" stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
                <rect x="62" y="2" width="4" height="64" fill="#F4EFE5"/>
                <g transform="translate(100, 34)">
                  <rect x="-12" y="-12" width="24" height="24" fill="none" stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
                  <rect x="-6" y="-6" width="12" height="12" fill="none" stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="1"/>
                </g>
                <text x="140" y="28" fill="#F4EFE5" font-family="'JetBrains Mono', ui-monospace, monospace" font-size="11" font-weight="500" letter-spacing="2">03</text>
                <text x="140" y="46" fill="#F4EFE5" font-family="'JetBrains Mono', ui-monospace, monospace" font-size="12" letter-spacing="2" opacity="0.95">BUILD</text>
                <text x="140" y="60" fill="#F4EFE5" font-family="'JetBrains Mono', ui-monospace, monospace" font-size="9" letter-spacing="1" opacity="0.55">SDLC inside · Design QA</text>
              </g>

              <!-- Connector arrow Build -> Measure -->
              <g transform="translate(240, 316)">
                <line x1="0" y1="0" x2="0" y2="12" stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" opacity="0.5"/>
                <polyline points="-4,8 0,12 4,8" fill="none" stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" opacity="0.5"/>
              </g>

              <!-- Phase 04: Measure -->
              <g transform="translate(0, 336)">
                <rect x="60" y="0" width="360" height="68" rx="4" fill="none" stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
                <rect x="62" y="2" width="4" height="64" fill="#E13D0F"/>
                <g transform="translate(100, 34)">
                  <line x1="-10" y1="10" x2="-10" y2="0" stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round"/>
                  <line x1="-3" y1="10" x2="-3" y2="-6" stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round"/>
                  <line x1="4" y1="10" x2="4" y2="-2" stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round"/>
                  <line x1="11" y1="10" x2="11" y2="-10" stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round"/>
                </g>
                <text x="140" y="28" fill="#E13D0F" font-family="'JetBrains Mono', ui-monospace, monospace" font-size="11" font-weight="500" letter-spacing="2">04</text>
                <text x="140" y="46" fill="#F4EFE5" font-family="'JetBrains Mono', ui-monospace, monospace" font-size="12" letter-spacing="2" opacity="0.95">MEASURE</text>
                <text x="140" y="60" fill="#F4EFE5" font-family="'JetBrains Mono', ui-monospace, monospace" font-size="9" letter-spacing="1" opacity="0.55">Invest · Iterate · Deprecate</text>
              </g>

              <!-- BOTTOM THREAD: Customer proximity (purple, dashed) -->
              <line x1="60" y1="420" x2="420" y2="420" stroke="#9B40C4" stroke-width="2" stroke-dasharray="4 4" stroke-linecap="round"/>
              <circle cx="240" cy="420" r="4" fill="#9B40C4"/>
              <text x="240" y="438" text-anchor="middle" fill="#9B40C4" font-family="'JetBrains Mono', ui-monospace, monospace" font-size="9" letter-spacing="2">CUSTOMER PROXIMITY · STANDING THREAD</text>
            </svg>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>

      <div class="mt-20 grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4 gap-6 pt-10 border-t border-cream/15 relative z-10">
        <div>
          <p class="eyebrow-light mb-2">Role</p>
          <p class="text-cream">Sr. Director, Product Experience</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="eyebrow-light mb-2">Duration</p>
          <p class="text-cream">Multi-quarter rollout</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="eyebrow-light mb-2">Team</p>
          <p class="text-cream">Product, Design, Eng, PMM</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="eyebrow-light mb-2">Outcome</p>
          <p class="text-cream">Adopted org-wide</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- =============================== -->
  <!-- The problem statement -->
  <!-- =============================== -->
  <section class="grid-backdrop border-b border-ink/10 overflow-hidden">
    <div class="grid-backdrop-band-top"></div>
    <div class="grid-backdrop-band-bottom"></div>
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 md:px-10 py-24 md:py-32 relative z-10">
      <p class="eyebrow mb-3">The problem we kept paying for</p>
      <h2 class="font-display text-display-md text-ink leading-tight max-w-[28ch] mb-12">
        Define was a black hole. Measurement was never the spine.
      </h2>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 max-w-5xl">
        <p class="text-xl text-ink-soft leading-relaxed">
          The company was shipping product, but problems got framed by PM alone.
          Designers entered at ticket assignment instead of problem framing.
          Engineers reacted to scoped solutions instead of shaping them.
          Analytics arrived after launch instead of before.
        </p>
        <p class="text-xl text-ink-soft leading-relaxed">
          The cost wasn't just velocity. Teams shipped features without success
          metrics, those features accumulated into a heavier and heavier system,
          and nothing got deprecated because nothing had been measured. The system
          got heavier every quarter.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- =============================== -->
  <!-- THE WORKSHOP METHODOLOGY -->
  <!-- =============================== -->
  <section class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 md:px-10 py-24 md:py-32">
    <p class="eyebrow mb-3">The approach</p>
    <h2 class="font-display text-display-md text-ink leading-tight max-w-[28ch] mb-12">
      You can't fix a process by writing a process doc in isolation.
    </h2>

    <div class="max-w-reading mb-16">
      <p class="text-xl text-ink-soft leading-relaxed">
        The work had to be grounded in how teams were actually working, where they
        were experiencing friction, and where expectations were misaligned. So
        instead of starting with a top-down framework, I designed a participatory
        workshop that asked each discipline to define its current reality first.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Three workshop prompts -->
    <div class="pillar-grid">

      <!-- Prompt 1 -->
      <div class="pillar">
        <div class="pillar-icon">
          <!-- Bullseye / purpose -->
          <svg viewBox="0 0 80 80" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
            <circle cx="40" cy="40" r="28" fill="#E13D0F" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="3"/>
            <circle cx="40" cy="40" r="18" fill="#F4EFE5" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="2.5"/>
            <circle cx="40" cy="40" r="10" fill="#E13D0F" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="2.5"/>
            <circle cx="40" cy="40" r="4" fill="#02101D"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <div class="pillar-meta">
          <p class="eyebrow mb-3">Prompt 01</p>
          <h3 class="font-display text-3xl text-ink leading-tight">
            What is the purpose of your role?
          </h3>
        </div>
        <div class="pillar-body">
          <p class="text-ink-soft leading-relaxed">
            Each discipline named what their role was ultimately responsible for.
            Not titles. Not tasks. The actual outcomes the role exists to create.
            This surfaced where role definitions had drifted from how teams
            described their own work.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="pillar-tagline"></div>
      </div>

      <!-- Prompt 2 -->
      <div class="pillar">
        <div class="pillar-icon">
          <!-- Calendar / week -->
          <svg viewBox="0 0 80 80" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
            <rect x="14" y="20" width="52" height="46" fill="#E13D0F" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="3"/>
            <rect x="14" y="20" width="52" height="10" fill="#02101D"/>
            <line x1="24" y1="14" x2="24" y2="26" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round"/>
            <line x1="56" y1="14" x2="56" y2="26" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round"/>
            <line x1="14" y1="40" x2="66" y2="40" stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="1.5" opacity="0.6"/>
            <line x1="14" y1="52" x2="66" y2="52" stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="1.5" opacity="0.6"/>
            <line x1="28" y1="30" x2="28" y2="66" stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="1.5" opacity="0.6"/>
            <line x1="42" y1="30" x2="42" y2="66" stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="1.5" opacity="0.6"/>
            <line x1="56" y1="30" x2="56" y2="66" stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="1.5" opacity="0.6"/>
            <circle cx="35" cy="46" r="3" fill="#02101D"/>
            <circle cx="49" cy="46" r="3" fill="#02101D"/>
            <circle cx="35" cy="58" r="3" fill="#02101D"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <div class="pillar-meta">
          <p class="eyebrow-voice mb-3">Prompt 02</p>
          <h3 class="font-display text-3xl text-ink leading-tight">
            What actually fills your week?
          </h3>
        </div>
        <div class="pillar-body">
          <p class="text-ink-soft leading-relaxed">
            The unedited version. What work actually consumed time. This surfaced
            the gap between the role's stated purpose and its lived reality.
            Designers logging hours on ticket triage. PMs spending weeks on docs
            instead of discovery. Engineers reverse-engineering missing context.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="pillar-tagline">
          <p class="font-display text-2xl italic text-orange">"The gap is the work."</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Prompt 3 -->
      <div class="pillar">
        <div class="pillar-icon">
          <!-- Crack / pain point -->
          <svg viewBox="0 0 80 80" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
            <rect x="14" y="14" width="52" height="52" fill="#E13D0F" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="3"/>
            <path d="M28 14 L 36 28 L 30 42 L 42 56 L 38 66" fill="none" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="4" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
            <circle cx="36" cy="28" r="3" fill="#02101D"/>
            <circle cx="30" cy="42" r="3" fill="#02101D"/>
            <circle cx="42" cy="56" r="3" fill="#02101D"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <div class="pillar-meta">
          <p class="eyebrow mb-3">Prompt 03</p>
          <h3 class="font-display text-3xl text-ink leading-tight">
            Where does the current process break down?
          </h3>
        </div>
        <div class="pillar-body">
          <p class="text-ink-soft leading-relaxed">
            Pain points named without filter. Late design involvement. Unclear
            exit criteria. PMM brought in after positioning had hardened. No
            success metrics before build. The honesty of this prompt did more
            for buy-in than any framework I could have presented.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="pillar-tagline"></div>
      </div>

    </div>

    <!-- The methodology in detail -->
    <div class="mt-20 grid md:grid-cols-12 gap-8 md:gap-16">
      <div class="md:col-span-4">
        <p class="eyebrow mb-3">The method</p>
        <h3 class="font-display text-2xl text-ink leading-tight">
          Sticky notes, by discipline, mapped to the lifecycle.
        </h3>
      </div>
      <div class="md:col-span-8">
        <div class="space-y-6">
          <div class="pb-6 border-b border-ink/10">
            <p class="font-mono text-xs text-orange uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">Step 01</p>
            <p class="font-display text-xl text-ink mb-2">Capture role-level input</p>
            <p class="text-ink-soft leading-relaxed">
              Participants used color-coded sticky notes by discipline (Product, Design, Engineering, PMM, Leadership). Each answered the three prompts individually before any group discussion. No solutions. No debate. Just current reality.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="pb-6 border-b border-ink/10">
            <p class="font-mono text-xs text-orange uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">Step 02</p>
            <p class="font-display text-xl text-ink mb-2">Cluster the themes</p>
            <p class="text-ink-soft leading-relaxed">
              Related notes were clustered into themes. Patterns emerged fast: discovery expectations varied widely, ownership was unclear, exit criteria were inconsistent, research and customer signal weren't integrated early enough, measurement wasn't defined before build.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="pb-6 border-b border-ink/10">
            <p class="font-mono text-xs text-orange uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">Step 03</p>
            <p class="font-display text-xl text-ink mb-2">Map work to the lifecycle</p>
            <p class="text-ink-soft leading-relaxed">
              Themes were mapped to lifecycle phases. Some pain points lived in one phase. Others showed up across multiple phases, revealing which parts of the process needed the most clarity. The map made the invisible rules of product development visible.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <p class="font-mono text-xs text-orange uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">Step 04</p>
            <p class="font-display text-xl text-ink mb-2">Define artifacts and exit criteria</p>
            <p class="text-ink-soft leading-relaxed">
              Once the current state was mapped, the group shifted from pain points to operating expectations. For each phase: what needs to be true before work moves forward, what decisions get made here, what artifacts exist, who owns them. This became the foundation for the four-phase model.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Workshop in action: three screenshots showing the arc -->
    <div class="mt-16 md:mt-20">
      <p class="eyebrow mb-3">The workshop in action</p>
      <h3 class="font-display text-2xl md:text-3xl text-ink leading-tight max-w-[42ch] mb-10">
        Setup. Current state. Future state. Three boards, one arc.
      </h3>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 md:gap-5">

        <!-- Board 1: Setup -->
        <figure>
          <button
            type="button"
            data-modal-trigger
            data-modal-src="/pdlc/workshop-step-1.png"
            data-modal-caption="Step 01 · Setup. Role purpose, work that fills the week, and pain points. Each discipline maps its current reality first."
            class="group block relative w-full bg-cream-warm/60 border border-ink/10 overflow-hidden aspect-[12/5] flex items-center justify-center transition-all hover:border-orange/40 hover:shadow-lg cursor-zoom-in"
            style="border-radius: 12px;"
            aria-label="View Step 01 Setup workshop board at full size"
          >
            <img
              src="/pdlc/workshop-step-1.png"
              alt="Workshop intro board showing the five-phase PDLC framework, instructions for the participatory workshop, and Step 1 individual input: role purpose, work that fills your week, and pain points organized by role using color-coded stickies"
              class="w-full h-full object-contain block transition-transform group-hover:scale-[1.02] pointer-events-none"
              loading="lazy"
            />
            <span class="absolute top-3 right-3 bg-ink/80 text-cream font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.12em] px-2 py-1 rounded opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 transition-opacity backdrop-blur-sm pointer-events-none">View full ↗</span>
          </button>
          <figcaption class="mt-4">
            <p class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.15em] text-orange mb-1">Step 01 · Setup</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-ink-soft leading-snug">Role purpose, work that fills the week, and pain points. Each discipline maps its current reality first.</p>
          </figcaption>
        </figure>

        <!-- Board 2: Map to PDLC -->
        <figure>
          <button
            type="button"
            data-modal-trigger
            data-modal-src="/pdlc/workshop-step-2.png"
            data-modal-caption="Step 02 · Current state. Map every sticky to the lifecycle phase where it happens. The concentration of work shows where the process actually breaks."
            class="group block relative w-full bg-cream-warm/60 border border-ink/10 overflow-hidden aspect-[12/5] flex items-center justify-center transition-all hover:border-orange/40 hover:shadow-lg cursor-zoom-in"
            style="border-radius: 12px;"
            aria-label="View Step 02 Current state workshop board at full size"
          >
            <img
              src="/pdlc/workshop-step-2.png"
              alt="Workshop board showing stickies clustered into the five PDLC phases of Discover, Define, Experiment, Deliver, and Monitor. Visible concentration of work and friction in the Define and Deliver phases"
              class="w-full h-full object-contain block transition-transform group-hover:scale-[1.02] pointer-events-none"
              loading="lazy"
            />
            <span class="absolute top-3 right-3 bg-ink/80 text-cream font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.12em] px-2 py-1 rounded opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 transition-opacity backdrop-blur-sm pointer-events-none">View full ↗</span>
          </button>
          <figcaption class="mt-4">
            <p class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.15em] text-orange mb-1">Step 02 · Current state</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-ink-soft leading-snug">Map every sticky to the lifecycle phase where it happens. The concentration of work shows where the process actually breaks.</p>
          </figcaption>
        </figure>

        <!-- Board 3: Phase Outcomes -->
        <figure>
          <button
            type="button"
            data-modal-trigger
            data-modal-src="/pdlc/workshop-step-3.png"
            data-modal-caption="Step 03 · Future state. For each phase: outcomes that must be true and artifacts that support them. Teal for outcomes. Orange for artifacts."
